        "text_8VXKAD": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h2><strong>Working Principle of Hakofyt Fertilizers</strong></h2><p><strong>Precisely Balanced Nutrient Ratio</strong></p><p>The effect of Hakofyt fertilizers is based on utilizing one of the fundamental principles of nutrition, known as <strong>Liebig’s Law of the Minimum</strong>. Its essence is that even though a plant may have most nutrients in surplus, its growth will be limited by the specific component that is insufficient.</p><p>Therefore, the goal in developing Hakofyt fertilizers was to ensure the most comprehensive plant nutrition possible. For this reason, in addition to basic macro-elements in optimal ratios—<strong>nitrogen, phosphorus, potassium, sulfur, and magnesium</strong>—Hakofyt fertilizers contain a complex of important micro-elements—specifically <strong>iron, zinc, manganese, copper, boron, and molybdenum</strong>, which are irreplaceable for the healthy and high-quality life of plants.</p>",
